baracuda-cutlass-kernels-sys
============================

The CUTLASS template instantiations under `kernels/` derive from NVIDIA's
CUTLASS examples (https://github.com/NVIDIA/cutlass), licensed under
BSD 3-Clause. CUTLASS itself is not redistributed — its headers are fetched
at build time by `baracuda-cutlass-sys`.

Vendored CUTLASS partial-specialization headers live under
`kernels/include/` and are also BSD-3-Clause (structure mirrors
upstream CUTLASS templates, re-specialized for SKUs CUTLASS's primary
dispatch chain doesn't route to):

- `baracuda_simt_broadcast_epilogue.h` — adds
  `DefaultGemmWithBroadcast` routing for `OperatorClass = OpClassSimt`,
  reaching CUTLASS's existing `DefaultEpilogueWithBroadcastSimt`.
- `baracuda_int8_rr_default_mma_core.h` — adds a partial specialization
  of `cutlass::gemm::threadblock::DefaultMmaCore` for `{int8_t, uint8_t}
  × RowMajor × {same} × RowMajor × OpClassTensorOp × Sm80` that swaps
  B's smem layout from `RowMajorTensorOpMultiplicandCongruous<8, _>` to
  `ColumnMajorTensorOpMultiplicandCrosswise<8, Shape::kK>` (K-contig in
  the smem PL view, what `mma.sync.m16n8k32.s8` expects). Bridges
  gmem→smem with `transform::TransposePitchLinearThreadMap`. Body
  structurally derived from CUTLASS's `RowMajor × RowMajor` spec at
  `default_mma_core_sm80.h:~1669` and the col-major-interleaved spec's
  transpose pattern at `~1821`. **Phase 2b-v2 WIP — the type chain
  compiles and the kernel runs, but the simple-transpose path produces
  random-pairing numerics on the GPU.** Need a custom transposing
  smem-store iterator (register-level `shfl.sync`) before this ships.
- `baracuda_int8_congruous_warp_iterator.h` — Phase 2b's vendored
  warp iterator for 8-bit `TensorOpMultiplicandCongruous<8, Crosswise>`
  smem. Not included by any current .cu — Congruous-8 smem layout
  itself is incompatible with the m16n8k32.s8 fragment expectation, so
  this artifact stays in tree as reference only.

The crate's API shape, plan-based architecture, and v0 SKU set
(`{f16, bf16} × RCR × {sm80, sm90a}` with Identity epilogue, grouped GEMM
as a first-class op with `prepare`/`run` separation and caller-supplied
workspace) were specified by the Fuel ML library team during baracuda's
Phase 4 design review. The Bias epilogue was originally planned but
removed during round-1 review (advertised but unimplemented); per the
team's roadmap it returns "after grouped GEMM lands and a real caller
asks for it." Grouped GEMM landed in 4d as the team's high-priority
deliverable for MoE workloads.

The build-time kernel-compilation infrastructure is provided by
`baracuda-forge`, which itself derives from `cudaforge` by Guoqing Bao.
See `crates/baracuda-forge/NOTICE` for that lineage.
